posts.author: David
posts.title: Gizmodo
posts.content: Originally launched as a part of Gawker Media Network, Gizmodo is a design, technology, science and science fiction website that also features articles on politics.

posts.author: Gluto
posts.title: 9to5Mac
posts.content: Founded by Seth Weintraub 13 years ago, 9to5Mac is the leading website within the Apple News Community in terms of breaking impactful news.

posts.author: Lily
posts.title: Mac Rumors
posts.content: Founded and owned by Arnold Kim, MacRumors attracts a broad audience of both consumers and professionals interested in the latest technologies and products.

posts.author: Williams
posts.title: Engadget
posts.content: An original home for technology news and reviews, Engadget produces the internet's most compelling videos, reviews, features and breaking news about the people, products and ideas shaping our world.

posts.author: Vinn
posts.title: Digital Trends
posts.content: Originally launched as a part of Gawker Media Network, Gizmodo is a design, technology, science and science fiction website that also features articles on politics.

posts.author: Akyy
posts.title: VentureBeat
posts.content: Founded 14 years ago, VentureBeat is the leading source for news, events, groundbreaking research and perspective on technology innovation.

posts.author: Selena
posts.title: The Verge
posts.content: The Verge is an ambitious multimedia effort founded nine years ago to examine how technology will change life in the future for a massive mainstream audience.

posts.author: Tom
posts.title: Apple Insider
posts.content: Launched over 20 years ago as a news and rumor website for Apple products and services, appleinsider.com includes a forum for discussion of news stories and other community news.

posts.author: David
posts.title: Mashable
posts.content: Mashable is a global, multi-platform media and entertainment company. Powered by its own proprietary technology, It is the go-to source for tech, digital culture and entertainment content.

posts.author: Lily
posts.title: SiliconANGLE
posts.content: SiliconAngle is a modern digital media platform that creates engaging social experiences for audiences through a depth of research, the reach of publishing, and relevance of live video.

posts.author: Lily
posts.title: TechCrunch
posts.content: Founded by Michael Arrington and later sold to AOL, TechCrunch has remained as one of the leaders covering tech industry news.

posts.author: David
posts.title: Android Authority
posts.content: With over 7 million followers on social sites, AndroidAuthority is the largest publication dedicated to the world's most widely used operating system.
